## Selenium Features

1. Selenium is an **open source** automation testing tool
2. It is exclusively for **web based applications**
3. It supports **multiple browsers**(chrome.safari, firefox, IE), **multiple platforms**(windows,linux,apple os), **multiple languages**(c#, python, java,php, ruby)

# Locators

Locators tell Selenium which element on the webpage you want to interact with.
In Java, they are used with the `By` class:

locators are the strategies used to find and interact with elements on a web page

### Types of locators

## 1.By.id

Locates an element using its id attribute.

Fastest and most preferred locator.
```
driver.findElement(By.id("email")).sendKeys("test@example.com");
```

## 2.By.name

Uses the elementâ€™s name attribute.
```
driver.findElement(By.name("password")).sendKeys("123456");
```

## 3.By.className

Finds elements by their CSS class value.

Not recommended if class names are long or dynamic.
```
driver.findElement(By.className("btn-login")).click();
```

## 4.By.tagName

Locates elements by their HTML tag (e.g., input, button, a).

Often used for retrieving multiple elements.
```
List<WebElement> links = driver.findElements(By.tagName("a"));
```

## 5.By.linkText

Used to locate links (<a> tag) using the exact visible text.
```
driver.findElement(By.linkText("Forgot Password")).click();
```
## 6.By.partialLinkText

Similar to linkText but matches partial visible text.
```
driver.findElement(By.partialLinkText("Forgot")).click();
```
## 7.By.cssSelector

Very powerful and flexible.

Often used when id/class is missing.

Supports complex queries.

Examples:
```
driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("#login"));          // id
driver.findElement(By.cssSelector(".btn.primary"));    // class
driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("input[type='text']"));
driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("div > ul li:first-child"));
```

## 8.By.xpath

Most powerful and flexible locator.

Can navigate the DOM tree.

Useful for dynamic elements when nothing else works.

Examples:

### Absolute XPath (not recommended)
```
driver.findElement(By.xpath("/html/body/div[1]/input"));
```

### Relative XPath (recommended)
```
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@id='username']"));
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//button[text()='Login']"));
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//div[@class='menu']//a[contains(text(), 'Home')]"));
```

| Priority | Locator         | Reason                                         |
| -------- | --------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | **id**          | Fastest, unique                                |
| 2        | **name**        | If id not available                            |
| 3        | **cssSelector** | Fast & powerful                                |
| 4        | **xpath**       | Most flexible, but slower                      |
| 5        | Others          | Use when necessary (linkText, className, etc.) |

   
